children.label: isCompatibleLicense
description:
Does this action factory license requirements
compatible with current license?

children.label: ui
description: UI State of the dynamic action manager.

children.label: generateActionId
description:
We prefix action IDs with a unique `.idPrefix`, so we can render the
same dashboard twice on the screen.

children.label: state
description:
Read-only state container of dynamic action manager. Use it to perform all
*read* operations.

children.label: start
description:
1. Loads all events from  @type {DynamicActionStorage} storage.
2. Creates actions for each event in `ui_actions` registry.
3. Adds events to UI state.
4. Does nothing if dynamic action manager was stopped or if event fetching
   is already taking place.

children.label: stop
description:
1. Removes all events from `ui_actions` registry.
2. Puts dynamic action manager is stopped state.

children.label: createEvent
description:
Creates a new event.

1. Stores event in @type {DynamicActionStorage} storage.
2. Optimistically adds it to UI state, and rolls back on failure.
3. Adds action to `ui_actions` registry.

children.label: action
description: Dynamic action for which to create an event.

children.label: triggers
description: List of triggers to which action should react.

children.label: updateEvent
description:
Updates an existing event. Fails if event with given `eventId` does not
exit.

1. Updates the event in @type {DynamicActionStorage} storage.
2. Optimistically replaces the old event by the new one in UI state, and
   rolls back on failure.
3. Replaces action in `ui_actions` registry with the new event.

children.label: eventId
description: ID of the event to replace.

children.label: action
description: New action for which to create the event.

children.label: triggers
description: List of triggers to which action should react.

children.label: deleteEvent
description:
Removes existing event. Throws if event does not exist.

1. Removes the event from @type {DynamicActionStorage} storage.
2. Optimistically removes event from UI state, and puts it back on failure.
3. Removes associated action from `ui_actions` registry.

children.label: eventId
description: ID of the event to remove.

children.label: deleteEvents
description: Deletes multiple events at once.

children.label: eventIds
description: List of event IDs.

classes.label: MemoryActionStorage
description:
This is an in-memory implementation of ActionStorage. It is used in testing,
but can also be used production code to store events in memory.

interfaces.label: ActionFactoryDefinition
description: This is a convenience interface for registering new action factories.

children.label: id
description:
Unique ID of the action factory. This ID is used to identify this action
factory in the registry as well as to construct actions of this type and
identify this action factory when presenting it to the user in UI.

children.label: minimalLicense
description:
Minimal license level
Empty means no license restrictions

children.label: licenseFeatureName
description:
Required when `minimalLicense` is used.
Is a user-facing string. Has to be unique. Doesn't need i18n.
The feature's name will be displayed to Cloud end-users when they're billed based on their feature usage.

children.label: isBeta
description:
Is this action factory not GA?
Adds a beta badge on a list item representing this ActionFactory

children.label: create
description:
This method should return a definition of a new action, normally used to
register it in `ui_actions` registry.

interfaces.label: BaseActionFactoryContext
description: Action factory context passed into ActionFactories' CollectConfig, getDisplayName, getIconType

interfaces.label: DrilldownDefinition
description:
This is a convenience interface to register a drilldown. Drilldown has
ability to collect configuration from user. Once drilldown is executed it
receives the collected information together with the context of the
user's interaction.

`Config` is a serializable object containing the configuration that the
drilldown is able to collect using UI.

`ExecutionContext` is an object created in response to user's interaction
and provided to the `execute` function of the drilldown. This object contains
information about the action user performed.

children.label: id
description: Globally unique identifier for this drilldown.

children.label: isBeta
description:
Is this action factory not GA?
Adds a beta badge on a list item representing this ActionFactory

children.label: minimalLicense
description:
Minimal license level
Empty means no restrictions

children.label: licenseFeatureName
description:
Required when `minimalLicense` is used.
Is a user-facing string. Has to be unique. Doesn't need i18n.
The feature's name will be displayed to Cloud end-users when they're billed based on their feature usage.

children.label: order
description:
Determines the display order of the drilldowns in the flyout picker.
Higher numbers are displayed first.

children.label: createConfig
description: Function that returns default config for this drilldown.

children.label: CollectConfig
isConfigValid
description:
A validator function for the config object. Should always return a boolean
given any input.

children.label: euiIcon
description: Name of EUI icon to display when showing this drilldown to user.

children.label: getDisplayName
description:
Should return an internationalized name of the drilldown, which will be
displayed to the user.

children.label: isCompatible
description:
isCompatible during execution
Could be used to prevent drilldown from execution

children.label: execute
description:
Implements the "navigation" action of the drilldown. This happens when
user clicks something in the UI that executes a trigger to which this
drilldown was attached.

children.label: config
description: Config object that user configured this drilldown with.

children.label: context
description:
Object that represents context in which the underlying
`UIAction` of this drilldown is being executed in.

children.label: getHref
description: A link where drilldown should navigate on middle click or Ctrl + click.

children.label: supportedTriggers
description:
List of triggers supported by this drilldown type
This is used in trigger picker when configuring drilldown

interfaces.label: UrlDrilldownGlobalScope
description:
Global static variables like, for example, `kibanaUrl`
Such variables wont change depending on a place where url drilldown is used.

interfaces.label: UrlDrilldownScope
description: URL drilldown has 3 sources for variables: global, context and event variables

children.label: context
description:
Dynamic variables that are differ depending on where drilldown is created and used,
For example: variables extracted from embeddable panel

children.label: event
description: Variables extracted from trigger context
